net.cloud.server.game.action

Class ButtonActionHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.cloud.server.game.action.ButtonActionHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ActionHandler<ButtonActionID>

    public class ButtonActionHandler
extends Object
implements ActionHandler<ButtonActionID>
    An ActionHandler dedicated to ButtonActions. Knows how to load them, store them, and pass off handling calls to them.

      • loadAllActions

        public void loadAllActions(PrintWriter out,
                           GroovyObjectLoader loader)
                    throws Exception
        Load all actions, one by one. This loads an action for each value in ButtonActionID. Continues even if one or more actions fail to load, instead concatenating all of the messages into the thrown exception.
        Specified by:
        loadAllActions in interface ActionHandler<ButtonActionID>
        Parameters:
        out - A PrintWriter to write output progress messages to
        loader - Used to obtain instances of the actions
        Throws:
        Exception - An exception if one or more button actions could not be loaded

        Load a single button action, replacing any existing action with the same ID. This is not thread safe... but if need ever be, just make the file name part synchronized
        Specified by:

      • handle

        public void handle(Player player,
                   ButtonActionID id,
                   Bufferable[] args,
                   io.netty.buffer.ByteBuf data)
            throws Exception
        Handle a button action by passing the call off to the ButtonAction object. If for some reason the action has not been loaded, then this call will terminate and do nothing. Normally, the action is asked to decode the provided data into the provided args array. Then, the action's handle method is called with the player and argument information.
        Parameters:
        player - The player performing this action
        id - The ID of the action
        args - Initialized array of arguments (may be null if not needed)
        data - Data that will be decoded into the arguments
        Throws:
        Exception - If something went wrong while handling the action
